INSERT INTO `activities` VALUES (1,'Hot Air Yoga ','Hot Air Yoga is very hot and very healthy!','45min',0),(2,'Pilates','Pilates is a physical fitness system developed by Joseph Pilates in the early 20th century. It focuses on strengthening the body with an emphasis on core stability, flexibility, balance, and posture. Pilates exercises can be performed on a mat or using specialized equipment such as the Reformer, Cadillac, and Wunda Chair.','45min',0),(3,'Abs','Working on your abdominal muscles (abs) at the gym can help you build core strength, improve posture, and enhance overall stability. A strong core supports your spine and can help prevent injuries during other workouts. Here are some effective exercises you can do in the gym to target your abs','30min',0),(4,'HIIT','High-intensity interval training (HIIT) is a popular and effective exercise strategy that alternates between short bursts of intense exercise and periods of rest or lower-intensity exercise. HIIT can be applied to various types of workouts, including cardio, strength training, and a combination of both.','30min',0),(5,'Indoor cycling','Indoor cycling, also known as spin class or spinning, is a group exercise that takes place on stationary bikes in a fitness studio or gym. It is a high-energy, motivating workout that combines cardiovascular training, strength endurance, and mental focus. Indoor cycling classes are often led by an instructor who guides participants through various resistance levels, speeds, and cycling techniques','45min',0),(6,'Boxing','Boxing is a combat sport that involves two individuals competing against each other by throwing punches while wearing gloves. It\'s a popular sport that combines athleticism, skill, and strategy. Boxing can also be an effective workout, providing a full-body exercise that improves cardiovascular health, strength, and coordination.','45min',0),(7,'Zumba','Zumba is a dance-fitness program that combines energetic dance moves with music from various genres, including Latin, hip-hop, pop, and international rhythms. It was created in the 1990s by Colombian dancer and choreographer Alberto. Zumba is a fun and effective workout that can improve cardiovascular health, coordination, and overall fitness.','60min',0),(8,'CrossFit','CrossFit is a high-intensity fitness program that combines elements of\n                weightlifting, gymnastics, and cardio. Workouts are varied and designed to improve\n                overall fitness and functional strength through constantly changing exercises.\n                CrossFit classes often involve short, intense bursts of exercise followed by rest or\n                lighter activity.','60min',0),(9,'TRX Training','TRX training uses suspension straps to perform bodyweight exercises that\n                challenge balance, flexibility, and core stability. The TRX system allows for a wide\n                range of exercises that can be adjusted for different fitness levels and target\n                various muscle groups.','60min',0),(10,'Kettlebell Training','Kettlebell training uses a cast-iron weight with a handle, known as a\n                kettlebell, to perform dynamic exercises. These workouts often involve swinging,\n                lifting, or pressing the kettlebell to improve strength, power, and endurance.\n                Kettlebell training also helps with balance and coordination.','45min',0),(14,'High Jump Training','High Jump training is very good for your cardiology health..','45min',0),(17,'High Intensive Training','High Jump training is very good for your cardiology health.','45min',0),(19,'Very Intensive Training','High Jump training is very good for your cardiology health.','45min',0),(21,'Group HIIT Training','GROUP HIIT Training is very good for your cardiology health.','45min',0);
